// <auto-generated>
// Rust port of the .NET ScriptAgent server. A standalone node that:
//   - binds the first free port in 5100-5200 and self-registers in
//     core.server_node as an `Agent` (status Online), like the API server;
//   - marks itself Offline on shutdown (SIGINT/SIGTERM);
//   - exposes the ScriptAgent REST surface. Most endpoints are stubs that return
//     the same placeholder shapes as the .NET controller; the load-bearing one is
//     `POST /api/scriptagent/execute`, which queues a workflow id for the
//     background execution thread.
//
// The execution thread runs `execute_workflow`: load the workflow -> its process
// -> its script, run the script through the shared `script` crate's ScriptHost
// (Rhai), then write the workflow's exec_status back and publish a notification
// so the web UI updates live. Internal reads/writes use the unchecked logic path
// (logic::object_exec_unchecked) because the agent runs as a trusted process with
// no security principal. Auth0 inbound validation is removed (as on the API).
// </auto-generated>
